On a lovely spring day this month, I was surprised by what I witnessed at South Africa’s first urban agricultural summit. Usually when I attend such meetings, I sit in a room full of professional food security experts, many of whom have never set foot on a farm and many of whom are men. Instead, at this convening, I sat with farmers who own and run thriving urban farming enterprises in Johannesburg.
 
